@startuml
title LogSys - WriteLog Sequence (Async Write Path)

participant Caller
participant LogManager
queue Channel as "queue chan LogEntry"
participant WriterLoop as "runWriteLoop() goroutine"
participant LogWriter
participant Handlers as "Registered LogHandlers"

Caller -> LogManager: WriteLog(level, message)
activate LogManager
LogManager -> LogManager: build LogEntry (from sync.Pool)
LogManager -> Channel: enqueue entry (non-blocking)
LogManager --> Caller: return (does not wait for I/O)
deactivate LogManager

== Background, decoupled from caller ==
activate WriterLoop
WriterLoop -> Channel: dequeue entry
WriterLoop -> LogWriter: Write(entry)
LogWriter --> WriterLoop: ok / error
WriterLoop -> Handlers: Handle(entry) for each registered handler
WriterLoop -> LogManager: release entry back to sync.Pool
deactivate WriterLoop

@enduml
